OL,3,CUK braced for record-breaking 40C as
OL,4,Cred weather warnings come into force
OL,6,FThe UK is braced for record-breaking
OL,7,Ftemperatures of up to 40C on Wednesday
OL,8,Fand Thursday, prompting schools to
OL,9,Fclose and people being urged not to
OL,10,Ftravel.
OL,12,FRare red weather warnings are in place
OL,13,Ffor parts of England and Wales, as a
OL,14,F"heat-dome" is settling over western
OL,15,FEurope.
OL,17,FThe Met Office issued red weather
OL,18,Fwarnings for extreme heat for an area
OL,19,Fstretching from London to Swansea and
OL,20,FSomerset to Birmingham from 9am on
OL,21,FWednesday to 9pm on Thursday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
