CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782341275
OL,3,CUK braced for record-breaking 40C as
OL,4,Cred weather warnings come into force
OL,6,FDuring the peak of the heatwave on
OL,7,Fthese two days, the temperature could
OL,8,Fcome close to the UK's all-time high
OL,9,Fof 40.3C, which was measured in
OL,10,FLincolnshire in July 2022.
OL,12,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,13,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,14,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,15,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,17,FThe latest heatwave is also expected
OL,18,Fto surpass the record for June of
OL,19,F35.6C set in Hampshire in 1976.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782341275
OL,3,CUK braced for record-breaking 40C as
OL,4,Cred weather warnings come into force
OL,6,FA combination of extreme heat and
OL,7,Fhumidity could impact public health,
OL,8,Finfrastructure, power and water
OL,9,Fsupplies, the Met Office said, and
OL,10,Fcause heat-related issues for a range
OL,11,Fof sectors such as transport, energy
OL,12,Fand water supply.
OL,14,FThere could also be an increase in
OL,15,Fwater safety incidents during the
OL,16,Fheatwave, the agency said, as more
OL,17,Fpeople are likely to visit coastal
OL,18,Fareas, lakes or rivers.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
