CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782341275
OL,3,CUK braced for record-breaking 40C as
OL,4,Cred weather warnings come into force
OL,6,FOn Tuesday the highest temperature
OL,7,Flogged was 34.6C in Wisley, Surrey,
OL,8,Faccording to the Met Office.
OL,10,FWhich areas will be worst affected?
OL,12,FRed heat health alerts have also been
OL,13,Fissued by the UK Health Security
OL,14,FAgency (UKHSA) for the East of
OL,15,FEngland, East Midlands, London, the
OL,16,FSouth East, the South West and the
OL,17,FWest Midlands, and amber heat health
OL,18,Falerts for the North East, North West,
OL,19,Fand Yorkshire and The Humber.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
