OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782341275
OL,3,CUK braced for record-breaking 40C as
OL,4,Cred weather warnings come into force
OL,6,FWest Midlands Railway said passengers
OL,7,Fshould check before they travel as
OL,8,Fextreme heat can cause rails to expand
OL,9,Fand buckle, so when temperatures reach
OL,10,Fcertain thresholds, trains must run
OL,11,Fmore slowly to keep services safe.
OL,13,FAnd Chiltern Railways said it had axed
OL,14,Fmore than half its services until
OL,15,FFriday "to ensure the safe operation
OL,16,Fof the railway".
OL,18,FEurostar has cancelled four trains
OL,19,Fplanned to run between London and
OL,20,FParis on Wednesday and Thursday "due
OL,21,Fto expected adverse weather".
OL,26,@wD@HOUxD@OO]|D@aOU}D@\O]
